{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.20",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 20 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:1",
      "text": "Then Sophar the Minaean answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:2",
      "text": "I did not suppose that thou wouldest answer thus: neither do ye understand more than I.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:3",
      "text": "I will hear my shameful reproach; and the spirit of my understanding answers me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:4",
      "text": "Hast thou not known these things of old, from the time that man was set upon the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:5",
      "text": "But the mirth of the ungodly is a signal downfall, and the joy of transgressors is destruction:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:6",
      "text": "although his gifts should go up to heaven, and his sacrifice reach the clouds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:7",
      "text": "For when he shall seem to be now established, then he shall utterly perish: and they that knew him shall say, Where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:8",
      "text": "Like a dream that has fled away, he shall not be found; and he has fled like a vision of the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:9",
      "text": "The eye has looked upon him, but shall not see him again; and his place shall no longer perceive him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:10",
      "text": "Let his inferiors destroy his children, and let his hands kindle the fire of sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:11",
      "text": "His bones have been filled with vigour of his youth, and it shall lie down with him in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:12",
      "text": "Though evil be sweet in his mouth, though he will hide it under his tongue;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:13",
      "text": "though he will not spare it, and will not leave it, but will keep it in the midst of his throat:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:14",
      "text": "yet he shall not at all be able to help himself; the gall of an asp is in his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:15",
      "text": "His wealth unjustly collected shall be vomited up; a messenger of wrath shall drag him out of his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:16",
      "text": "And let him suck the poison of serpents, and let the serpent’s tongue slay him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:17",
      "text": "Let him not see the milk of the pastures, nor the supplies of honey and butter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:18",
      "text": "He has laboured unprofitably and in vain, for wealth of which he shall not taste: it is as a lean thing, unfit for food, which he cannot swallow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:19",
      "text": "For he has broken down the houses of many mighty men: and he has plundered an habitation, though he built it not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:20",
      "text": "There is no security to his possessions; he shall not be saved by his desire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:21",
      "text": "There is nothing remaining of his provisions; therefore his goods shall not flourish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:22",
      "text": "But when he shall seem to be just satisfied, he shall be straitened; and all distress shall come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:23",
      "text": "If by any means he would fill his belly, let God send upon him the fury of wrath; let him bring a torrent of pains upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:24",
      "text": "And he shall by no means escape from the power of the sword; let the brazen bow wound him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:25",
      "text": "And let the arrow pierce through his body; and let the stars be against his dwelling-place: let terrors come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:26",
      "text": "And let all darkness wait for him: a fire that burns not out shall consume him; and let a stranger plague his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:27",
      "text": "And let the heaven reveal his iniquities, and the earth rise up against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:28",
      "text": "Let destruction bring his house to an end; let a day of wrath come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.20.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:29",
      "text": "This is the portion of an ungodly man from the Lord, and the possession of his goods appointed him by the all-seeing God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
